Sentencas: A finite element model has been developed to simulate the steady state and impedance behaviour of a single operating solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC).

Sentencas: The model results suggest that electrode delamination can be detected minimally-invasively by using electrochemical impedance spectroscopy.

Sentencas: The presence of cathode delarnination causes changes in the cell impedance spectrum that are characteristic of this type of degradation mechanism.

Sentencas: These changes include the simultaneous increase in both the series and polarization resistances, in proportion to the delaminated area.

Sentencas: Parametric studies show the dependence of these changes on the extent of delamination, on the operating point, and on the kinetic characteristics of the fuel cell under study.
